    "recap_headline": "University of North Carolina Ashville Athletics",
    "recap_text": "ASHEVILLE, N.C. -\nUNC Asheville Baseball dropped its rubber match to Villanova on Sunday (Mar. 22) by a score of 11-6.\nEach team scored one run in the first inning, with an\nOwen Michelson\ngroundout scoring\nLogan Lowe\nto score the game's first run. Villanova scored one run in the bottom of the first to tie the game, before the teams traded scoreless frames in the second. Villanova responded with four runs in the bottom of the third to take the lead, before the teams again traded scoreless frames in the fourth. After Villanova added one in the fifth, Asheville responded with three runs in the top of the sixth to cut into the lead.\nBlaize Johnson\nled off the inning with a walk, before Michelson would draw a one-out walk and\nJake Minarik\nwas hit by a pitch to load the bases.\nBen Green\ngrounded out to bring Johnson, before Michelson scored on a wild pitch. Minarik would later score on a wild pitch to cap off the inning. Villanova would pull away in the game with five runs in the bottom of the sixth. Asheville would score one run in the seventh and one in the ninth to bring the game to its final score.\nPatrick Gillen\nbrought home\nLogan Lowe\non a RBI single in the seventh, before Green singled home Lowe in the ninth.\nGillen paced the offense with three hits including one double, Lowe and Green had two hits each and\nZeb Swangim\nalso had one hit. Green drove in two runs in the game, while Gillen also drove in one. Lowe scored three times in the game, while Johnson, Michelson and Minarik each scored once.\nDrew Turner\n(3-3) took the loss on the bump, before handing the ball off to\nBen Green\nfor two innings of relief.\nTJ Brooks\nfinished the game with a hitless inning of relief picking up one strikeout.\nThe Bulldogs (12-12) return to action on Tuesday (Mar. 24) hosting Western Carolina in non-conference action. First pitch is set for 4:00 p.m. from Greenwood Field, with\nvideo\nand\nlive stats\navailable at\nwww.uncabulldogs.com\n.",
